---
import { metrics } from '../data/landingContent';
---

<section id="indicadores" class="section-watermark section-watermark--blue relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-18 lg:px-8 lg:py-24 reveal-up" data-delay="100">
  <div class="metrics-panel border-y border-[var(--color-line)] py-10 md:py-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl reveal-left" data-delay="100">
      <span class="eyebrow">Indicadores</span>
      <h2 class="section-title mt-6 text-4xl leading-tight font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] md:text-5xl">
        La confianza tambien se construye con indicadores visibles
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-[var(--color-muted)]">
        En el sitio actual falta convertir fortalezas en señales rapidas de credibilidad. Aqui las llevamos a metricas claras y faciles de escanear.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-0 border-t border-[var(--color-line)] md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4" data-stagger>
      {metrics.map((metric, index) => (
        <article class="metric-card border-b border-[var(--color-line)] px-1 py-7 md:px-6 xl:border-b-0 xl:border-r xl:last:border-r-0 reveal-up" data-stagger-item data-delay={index * 80}>
          <p
            class="text-4xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] md:text-5xl metric-value"
            data-counter
            data-value={metric.value.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '')}
            data-suffix={metric.value.includes('%') ? '%' : metric.value.includes('/') ? '/7' : ''}
            aria-label={metric.value}
          >{metric.value}</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-[var(--color-muted)]">{metric.label}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
